Joey Jay is the stage name of Joey Jadryev, an American drag performer most known for competing on season 13 of RuPaul's Drag Race.
Early life
Joey Jadryev was born in Madison, Wisconsin. He began performing in drag while living in Milwaukee before moving to Phoenix, Arizona with plans to open a ballroom dancing studio, a plan that fell through due to injury.
Career
Prior to pursuing drag, Jadryev worked as an account manager at a software company.
Joey Jay performs at Kobalt Bar in Phoenix, Arizona. She competed on season 13 of RuPaul's Drag Race. She was eliminated on the fifth episode after losing a lip-sync to "Fancy" by Iggy Azalea against LaLa Ri.
In 2024, Joey Jay lobbied for LGBTQ+ rights alongside Jiggly Caliente and Brigitte Bandit at the United States Capitol. In drag pageantry, she was crowned Miss Gay Phoenix America 2025.
Personal life
Jadryev is openly gay, Jewish, and lived in Milwaukee before moving to Phoenix in 2017.
